Get ready for the ultimate test of endurance and skill in the Water Triathlon during AdventureFest on the Redlands Coast! This exciting event combines three exhilarating water activities: Kayak, Water Bike, and Paddleboard, taking you through the stunning waters of Moreton Bay Marine Park.

Kick off with a thrilling kayak leg, paddling your way through the pristine waters, then jump on a water bike for a fast-paced 100-meter sprint. Finish strong with a paddleboard leg, gliding your way across the bay to complete the final stretch of this exciting triathlon.

This race is perfect for anyone, whether you're a seasoned athlete or just looking to have fun and try something new. The breathtaking views of Moreton Bay Marine Park, with Stradbroke Island and Moreton Island's sandy dunes in the distance, providing the perfect backdrop for this action-packed event. You may even spot the dolphins playing, or turtles and dugongs popping up for a look.

$10 to entercall to secure your place in the race. Plus it's free to come and watch, so bring your friends, family, and supporters to cheer you on!

Join in on 25th May for a day of fitness, fun, and unforgettable memories. Plus, you'll have the chance to compete for amazing prizes, including the Water Bike Time Trials winner's exclusive reward (valued at $500)!

_source.productDescription:
Join in at Munimba-ja for a full day around the fire for a conscious clap stick gathering with Aunty Dinnawhan (emu woman), a Waka - Kabi elder.

Come celebrate creating enchanting sounds and rhythms with your own clap sticks. Connecting to Country through the knowledge of dau'wa dhu (dry wood/trees) Connecting with the sacred wood for clap stick medicine. 

You'll get to choose your timber from various tree species provided and be shown how to use hand tools to cut and shape your own personalised clapsticks. Once you are happy with the size and shape of your clapsticks, Aunty Dinnawhan will lead you through mark making using wood burning tools and how to finish and seal using natural oils. 

What's included:
Connection to country and cleansing
Calling in the wood ceremony
Yarning the origins of the clap stick 
Dancing to their sacred vibrational sounds
Damper by the fire cooked by Aunty plus lemon myrtle tea
Morning and afternoon tea provided. 
Variety of woods 
Sandpaper, knives, tomahawks, various files (but bring your favourite carving knife if you have one)
Woodburning tools for burning stories into clapsticks

Experiencing:
Sacred dhur (circle) business 
Connection to country through your clapsticks
Sharing and caring for each other
Lots of love, fun, laughter and creativeness

One weekend in May and November each year is the golden opportunity for wine and food enthusiasts to taste their way around Granite Belt Wine Country all in one ticket.

This ticket grants unlimited use of the shuttles operating on a continuous loop to let you indulge in tastings at boutique cellar doors and graze away on local gourmet produce.

Ticket holders 'lazy graze' their way between the local boutique wineries on Saturday, with unlimited use of the bus loop. Typically 7 - 10 venue stops are on the bus loop.  Each ticket includes a voucher book to use along the way, including 4 dishes and 4 drink pours, plus Sunday brunch.

Each venue offers a special Grazing menu, featuring entre-sized dishes perfectly pairing with one of the venue's wines or beers. 

The buses begin and end their loop at the Stanthorpe Visitor Information Centre.

Ticket holders can collect all wine purchases made from one location before brunch on the Sunday morning of the event.
